    "body": "When the client starts up it checks for rollback and if it is necessary it will do that(core/blockchain.go: bc.Rollback(hashes)). Usually, you don't need to do anything. Also, there is a file named blocks.go in the core directory that consists of a map and if you want to ban some block hashes you can add the hash to this map, in a startup, the client will get back to one block before that blocks. (core/blockchain.go - NewBlockChain function)",
